ed and treated globally, these artists emphasize ethical relations between strangers and ask viewers to question their own place within unjust social orders.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArt and race. 0aArt and societyxHistoryy21st century. 0aArtxPolitical aspects. 0aElectronic surveillancexSocial aspects. 0aSocial practice (Art) 0aSocial practice (Art). 0aSurveillance in artxSocial aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Privacy & Surveillance (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Privacy & Surveillance) .2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076691208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478023388?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478023388423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478023388/original  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099455-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DSLb2022